'''Chris Slane''' (born 1957) is a left wing [[New Zealand]] [[cartoonist]].

He has had cartoons published in ''[[Metro (magazine, NZ)|Metro]]'', ''[[New Zealand Herald]]'' and ''AA Directions'' magazine. Slane is currently the cartoonist for the ''[[New Zealand Listener]]'' and ''New Zealand Farmers Weekly''.

He has a degree in town planning from the [[University of Auckland]], and contributed to the student magazine ''[[Craccum]]'' while studying there.

==Bibliography==
